WEBVTT

00:00:00.450 --> 00:00:04.890
A tidal boundary drives a hydraulic pressure wave inland through the aquifer.

00:00:05.300 --> 00:00:11.612
Yet one signal yielded two diffusivities: one from amplitude decay, the other from phase lag.

00:00:12.050 --> 00:00:18.626
Nature had not changed. The classical model forced both observations into instantaneous equilibrium.

00:00:21.050 --> 00:00:29.234
Real aquifers contain preferential flow paths, low-permeability interfaces, and dual-porosity systems. They need not equilibrate together.

00:00:29.950 --> 00:00:37.390
Two causal clocks replace one: flux equilibration along preferential paths, and matrix-fracture pressure equilibration.

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:40.524
Different periods reveal different memories.

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:47.668
At the Meghna River, the classical diffusivity was nearly eighty times larger, yet still overdamped the signal.

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:54.250
The aquifer did not contradict itself. The one-clock model did.
